  "body": "Create a lodecli configuration\r\nEdit beacon.config.json, add \"chain.params.GENESIS_FORK_VERSION\": \"0x00000113\"\r\nRun beacon node, should error w/ something like \"value.replace is not a function\"\r\n\r\nThe reason is we're not setting the option type in `lodestar-cli/src/lodecli/cmds/beacon/cmd/run/options/params.ts`, and yargs parses hex strings into numbers if a \"type\" is not set.\r\n\r\nQuick fix would be to add something like `type: Buffer.isBuffer(params[key]) ? \"string\" : undefined`\r\nIdeally, we would have a more systematic way of handling params of different types, rather than inspecting runtime values of mainnet config.",
